Cant push another PR while this waiting something. Are NB is alive?
@mbien 
@BradWalker

looks good to me. I suppose the only way to change the offset again once the server has been created is by editing the config xml?

@akronenw' are you ok with this implementation too? Does it solve your issue of not being able to restart the server?

(fixed some UI issues while looking at this #5608)

Well, with this last commit I think we're ready to merge to master and continue evolving there.

We can now pass commit-validation tests in both the `release` and `full` cluster configurations.

@mbien @matthiasblaesing , I'd appreciate a second review.

@BradWalker my original plan was to mark the changes in the screenshot. But after taking so many it would have been too much work using gimp. The second idea was to use the `mouseover` feature of the img tag to switch between images on hover, but github doesn't support it either.

So the easiest way to see the difference is to download the zip, open an image with a viewer tool and quickly toggle with the  arrow keys between before/after. Some changes only make sense in context, e.g if you switch between tabs in the UI.

Looking at the linked issue can also help to know what to look for.

@eirikbakke the UI snapshot feature of the debugging session was vital to find where stuff is implemented. It allows to jump directly to the implementation. Although some layout issues were super sneaky, e.g some code somewhere else adding a empty border with insets to patch something, or even worse: code replacing components, borders or even layout managers outside of the actual component code.

thanks everyone for review. I will do another manual test and then merge.
